-- Polish Stocks: KGHM, PGE Power Utility Shares Move in Warsaw
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-05-28T09:56:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-28/polish-stocks-kghm-pge-power-utility-shares-move-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  rose 0.8 percent
to 2,052.45 at 11:16 a.m. in Warsaw, advancing for a second day.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
Warsaw Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH)  , the country’s sole copper
and silver producer, climbed 1.3 percent to 119.7 zloty, rising
the most in a week on a closing basis as the two metals advanced
after Greek opinion polls showed greater support for pro-bailout
parties.  PGE SA (PGE)  , the nation’s largest electricity producer,
surged 2.2 percent to 17.53 zloty, gaining the most in more than
two weeks after the company said it has many potential bidders
for a stake in its power plant project.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
